column18: What is your annual household income?
column19: What was your overall impression of this event (quality, lighting, sound, value)?
column20: Please share any other suggestions or ideas that would help us enhance your experience at Gesa Power House Theatre. If you would like someone to respond to your feedback, please include your contact information. Thank you!

column19: Fantastic!  Energy, positive vibes, great entertainers, what a fun night.
Great all of it was wonderful. Thank you for keeping the arts alive in WW. Especially cultural.
The show was AMAZING! Excellent performers. Sound and lighting were solid. It got pretty hot toward the end of the show.
column20: Better fan in the women’s restroom. Someone destroyed it and the smell was overpowering.

column19: The group was fantastic! The lights were not. The sound was fine, but lead male was hard to hear at times. The show was well worth the money.
It was good & highlighted the singers just right.
column20: The Cafeteras are an awesome Band show.  I wish there had been more marketing on their music to the WW, M-F & Tri-Cities region.  I think you would have been completely sold out.  There would have been more of Hispanic turn out even if it was on a Thursday.  I would most definitely go again if they come back to WW.  Thank you so much for bringing them to WW Gesa Power House Theatre...  & for all you do for our WW Region in the ARTS.

column19: Beyond wonderful - I'm using a MAC and somehow deleted a nice bit about how wonderful it was.....chat later.
column20: Consider having a few tables and chairs out on the balcony/patio with the door open to allow guests to enjoy the beautiful weather and meet.  I understand that it was too windy for the front yard.

column19: Great-haven't seen that much energy on the stage for a long time.
